title: Frigidaire Freezer Gallery model not freezing

full_content.content: Frigidaire Freezer Gallery model not freezing
Common reasons your Frigidaire Freezer Gallery model not freezing
The most common reasons your Frigidaire Gallery model freezer is not freezing are a failed compressor start relay, malfunctioning electronic control board or a bad thermostat.
We can help! Our service technicians have repaired over 15,000 Frigidaire freezers. We can fix yours no matter where you bought it.
Most common repairs needed to fix a Frigidaire freezer

When your Frigidaire Gallery model freezer is not freezing and you don’t hear the compressor running, a bad compressor start relay could be preventing the compressor from starting. The compressor start relay sends current to the motor start windings to boost motor torque to start the motor, and to the motor run windings. Once the motor starts, the relay continues to send current to the run windings, but cuts off current to the start windings. A defective start relay won't send current to the start windings, run windings or both. The start relay includes an overload component that shuts off all current to the motor if the motor overheats. A defective overload trips when the motor isn't overheated, preventing the motor from starting. Have a Sears Home Services technician check the compressor start relay and replace it if it’s bad.
How to replace a freezer compressor start relay

When your Frigidaire Gallery model freezer is not freezing, a malfunctioning electronic control board could be causing the problem. The electronic control board receives signals from various sensors to monitor the temperature inside the freezer. Using the information it receives from these sensors, the board starts or stops the compressor, fans, defrost cycle and other components. A bad internal relay or corrupted internal logic on the circuit board can prevent the electronic control board from sending electric current to the compressor for cooling. When your freezer isn’t cooling, schedule service through Sears Home Services. Our technician will visit your home and fix the cooling problem in your freezer.
How to replace a freezer electronic control board

When your Frigidaire Gallery model freezer is not freezing, a bad cold control thermostat may be causing the issue. The cold control thermostat senses freezer interior temperature and cycles the compressor on and off to maintain the set temperature on the thermostat dial. A faulty thermostat may not be sensing freezer temperature properly or may not be sending current to the compressor properly to cool the freezer. When your freezer sometimes runs but is not freezing, schedule freezer repair service to have a Sears Home Services technician fix the cooling problem.
How to replace a freezer cold control thermostat
What to expect when you experience a Frigidaire Gallery model freezer not freezing issue
How is the not freezing problem fixed?

Correcting most not freezing problems usually involves replacing the compressor start relay, electronic control board or thermostat. However, there are many potential causes, so a thorough diagnosis is key to fixing the problem. An accurate diagnosis is essential to understanding how much the repair will be.
Sears Home Services recommendations for a Frigidaire Gallery model freezer not freezing

When the freezer is not freezing it can be for many reasons. To avoid replacing unneeded parts we recommend having a Sears Home Services professional perform diagnostic tests to identify the root cause of the problem. Our technicians are experienced at diagnosing all types of freezer failures.
What to look out for with a freezer not cooling diagnosis

Diagnosing modern appliances without proper knowledge and training can be difficult. Without using proper diagnostic techniques, fixing your freezer problem will only be achieved through changing parts on a hunch. Appliances, especially in the last 10 years, have become extremely advanced, and many models have electronic parts that are difficult to test. DIY repairs on the latest appliance models are becoming increasingly difficult.

full_content.content: Why isn’t my Frigidaire Gallery freezer reaching freezing temperatures?
Blocked air vents, a malfunctioning evaporator fan motor, or low refrigerant can prevent proper freezing. Check that vents aren’t blocked by stored items.
How do I verify the evaporator fan is running?
Listen for the fan when the freezer is on. If it’s silent, inspect behind the freezer panel for motor or blade issues. Replace if defective.
Does a sealed system leak affect freezing?
Yes. If refrigerant levels drop, cooling capacity declines. Only certified technicians can repair sealed system leaks and recharge refrigerant safely.
When should I call a pro for a Frigidaire Gallery freezer not freezing?
If you’ve confirmed airflow and fan functionality but still lack freezing temps, the compressor or sealed system may be compromised. A qualified appliance repair tech can handle complex repairs.

full_content.content: How Do Chest Freezers Work?: 2025 Explanation
Learn how chest freezers work and how to troubleshoot common problems.

A freezer bag is a specially designed plastic bag used for the cold storage of food in the freezer, offering protection against freezer burn and preserving the food's freshness and flavor over extended periods.

A freezer compressor is a vital component of a freezer's refrigeration system, functioning as a pump to circulate refrigerant through the system, which cools the interior by absorbing and expelling heat.
What is a Freezer Door Gasket?
A freezer door gasket is a flexible seal that outlines the edge of the freezer door, ensuring an airtight closure to maintain cold temperatures inside and prevent warm air from entering.
What is a Manual Defrost Freezer?
A manual defrost freezer is an appliance that needs to be switched off and allowed to thaw periodically to remove accumulated ice, ensuring efficient operation and storage space maximization.
